        "jd":  "What do we do?\n\nIntroducing Thinkproject Platform\n\nPioneering a new era and offering a cohesive alternative to the fragmented landscape of construction software, Thinkproject seamlessly integrates the most extensive portfolio of mature solutions with an innovative platform, providing unparalleled features, integrations, user experiences, and synergies.\n\nBy combining information management expertise and in-depth knowledge of the building, infrastructure, and energy industries, Thinkproject empowers customers to efficiently deliver, operate, regenerate, and dispose of their built assets across their entire lifecycle through a Connected Data Ecosystem.\n\nWhat your day will look like\n\nMission\n\nAs Customer Insight \u0026 Adoption Lead (f/m/d), you will be responsible for ensuring that what we build genuinely reflects customer needs and delivers real user value. You will act as the voice of the customer within Product and Engineering, grounding product decisions in evidence, insight, and continuous feedback rather than assumptions.\n\nThis is a hands-on role focused on deeply understanding user needs, behaviours, and pain points, and ensuring those insights directly influence product direction, UX decisions, and delivery priorities. You will work closely with Product Managers and the UI/UX team, and you will own structured customer engagement mechanisms such as customer councils and early adopter programmes to keep us closely connected to our users. You will bring a high degree of personal ownership and initiative, thriving in environments with autonomy, ambiguity, and a strong bias toward action and outcomes.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nCustomer Insight \u0026 Discovery\n\n\nOwn the collection, synthesis, and communication of customer and user insights across the product organisation.\nWork directly with customers and end users to understand needs, workflows, pain points, and unmet expectations.\nPlan and conduct qualitative and quantitative research activities in partnership with Product Managers such as interviews, usability testing, surveys, and discovery sessions.\nTranslate customer insights into clear, actionable inputs for Product Managers and UX designers.\nContinuously validate assumptions and ensure product decisions are grounded in real user evidence.\n\n\nProduct \u0026 UX Collaboration\n\n\nPartner closely with Product Managers to shape problem statements, priorities, and roadmap decisions based on customer insight.\nWork hand in hand with the UI/UX team to inform user journeys, interaction design, and usability improvements.\nEnsure customer feedback is considered early in discovery, not just after delivery.\nSupport Product Managers with insight-backed narratives for trade-offs and prioritisation decisions.\n\n\nCustomer Council \u0026 Early Adopter Programmes\n\n\nOwn and manage customer councils, advisory boards, and early adopter programmes.\nRecruit, engage, and maintain strong relationships with representative customers and user groups.\nDefine clear objectives, formats, and cadences for customer council sessions to maximise insight and value.\nEnsure feedback from councils and early adopters is captured, synthesised, and fed back into product and UX work.\nClose the loop with participants by communicating outcomes and demonstrating how their input influenced decisions.\n\n\nAdoption \u0026 Feedback Loops\n\n\nMonitor how customers adopt and use new features and capabilities post-release.\nPartner with Product, UX, and Services teams to identify adoption issues and usability gaps.\nFeed adoption insights back into product improvement cycles and roadmap refinement.\nHelp define success metrics related to user value, adoption, and satisfaction, and work with Product and Engineering to incorporate the necessary instrumentation into our Products.\n\n\nInsight Enablement \u0026 Ways of Working\n\n\nEstablish lightweight, repeatable processes for capturing, storing, and sharing customer insights.\nImprove visibility of customer needs and feedback across Product, Engineering, and Leadership.\nPromote a culture of customer-centricity and evidence-based decision making.\nAdvocate for continuous discovery as a core part of how products are built.\n\n\nWhat you need to fulfill the role\n\nEssential\n\n\nProven experience in a customer insight, user research, product discovery, or similar hands-on role.\nStrong ability to engage directly with customers and users and build trust-based relationships.\nExperience translating customer research into clear, actionable insights for product and UX teams.\nComfort working closely with Product Managers and designers in an agile, product-led environment.\nExcellent communication and facilitation skills, both written and verbal.\nAbility to synthesise large amounts of qualitative feedback into clear themes and recommendations.\nStrong organisational skills and ability to manage multiple feedback streams in parallel.\nFluent German \u0026 English required.\n\n\nBonus\n\n\nExperience running customer councils, advisory boards, or early adopter programmes.\nBackground in UX research, service design, or human-centred design practices.\nFamiliarity with SaaS or enterprise software products.\nExperience working with usage data, analytics, or adoption metrics alongside qualitative insight.\nFamiliarity with construction, infrastructure, or asset lifecycle management software.\n\n\nWhat we offer\n\nLunch \u0027n\u0027 Learn Sessions I Women\u0027s Network I LGBTQIA+ Network I Coffee Chat Roulette I Free English Lessons I Thinkproject Academy I Social Events I Volunteering Activities I Open Forum with Leadership Team (Tp CafèŒ…) I Hybrid working I Unlimited learning\n\nWe are a passionate bunch here. To join Thinkproject is to shape what our company becomes. We take feedback from our staff very seriously and give them the tools they need to help us create our fantastic culture of mutual respect. We believe that investing in our staff is crucial to the success of our business.\n\nYour Contact\n\nYash Shetty\n\nPlease submit your application, including salary expectations and potential date of entry, by submitting the form on the next page.\n\nWorking at thinkproject.com - think career. think ahead.\n\n\néˆ¥?more"
