        "jd":  "Responsibilities / Tasks\n\nWe are looking for a highly skilled Process Integration Manager (PIM) (f/m/d) to strengthen our global SAP rollout organization. In this role, you will drive endéˆ¥و†ˆoéˆ¥و…¹nd process alignment across multiple process areas and ensure that our SAP template is consistently implemented across diverse business units and regions.\n\nThe PIM function becomes active whenever a topic touches more than two process houses, requires cross-functional alignment, or lacks a clear endéˆ¥و†ˆoéˆ¥و…¹nd owner. You will act as moderator, integrator, and orchestrator, ensuring that engineering, procurement, production, logistics, finance, and service work seamlessly together in our Engineeréˆ¥و†ˆoéˆ¥و…œrder (ETO) environment.\n\nThis role is ideal for someone who enjoys complex challenges, builds alignment across functions, and ensures stable and scalable process execution.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\n\nEnd-to-End Integration \u0026 Governance\nLead and coordinate cross-process SAP integration topics across the ETO value chain (from bid management to engineering, procurement, production, project delivery, and after-sales service).\nGovern ETO process flows within SAP, ensuring alignment between Engineering, Sourcing, Production, Logistics, Finance, Controlling, and Service.\nIdentify process integration gaps and ensure consistent and scalable process design within the SAP template.\nDrive continuous improvement across supply chain, production, engineering, and project controlling processes.\n\n\nCrosséˆ¥و…’unctional Facilitation \u0026 Orchestration\n\n\nModerate workshops involving multiple process houses to define scope, acceptance criteria, dependencies, and solution paths.\nAlign stakeholders in topics where éˆ¥و¸†veryone is involved but no one is in the lead.éˆ¥و¼’nBreak down E2E requirements into actionable work packages, assign them to the appropriate workstreams, and steer execution.\n\n\nData Governance \u0026 Consistency\n\n\nEnsure proper data ownership and governance across master data domains:\nMaterials\nProjects\nWork centers\nVendors\nCustomers\nSupport harmonization and standardization of data structures required for ETO processes.\n\n\nRisk, Escalation \u0026 Change Management\n\n\nProactively identify risks, integration gaps, and crosséˆ¥و†„rocess dependencies.\nManage conflicts and competing priorities across functions and regions.\nInitiate escalations where needed (e.g., resource constraints, conflicting goals, missed deadlines).\nPrepare cross-functional topics and change requests for decision-making in the established governance bodies.\n\n\nYour Profile / Qualifications\n\n\nStrong cross process experience in SAP implementation projects, ideally in an Engineer to Order (ETO) or project-driven manufacturing environment.\nProven experience in leading cross-functional process workshops and integration discussions.\nAbility to translate complex technical SAP concepts into clear, business-oriented explanations.\n\n\nSoft Skills\n\n\nExcellent stakeholder management across engineering, operations, finance, service, and IT.\nNatural facilitator with strong conflict resolution and negotiation skills in high complexity environments.\nStrong communication skills, especially in explaining E2E processes to non-experts.\nLeadership in international and matrix organizations.\nProactive risk identification, structured problem solving, and strong ownership mindset.\nEffective change agent, capable of driving adoption of new processes and harmonization across global teams.\n\n\nWe Are Looking For\n\n\na connector who enjoys navigating complexity\na pragmatic problem-solver who brings structure to ambiguity\na communicator who builds alignment across functions and cultures\na process thinker who sees the big picture, not just system transactions\na team player who naturally steps into the lead where no clear owner exists\n\n\nWhat We Offer\n\n\nWork with a supportive and international team\nModern working environment with flexible working options and home office for a good work-life balance (3:2)\n30 vacation days\nAttractive company benefits such as discounts on gym memberships, courses, etc.\nJobRad including subsidy\n\n\nWhat happens once your application is submitted?\n\nYou will receive an E-Mail when your application has been processed. One of our Talent Acquisition Specialists will review and verify that the applicant meets the qualifications criteria. Once your application has been successfully verified and depending on the role you will be invited to a first interview either virtual or face to face. Usually after the second or third interview round we will make a decision.\n\n\nFor reasons of readability, no gender-specific differentiation is made in the job advertisement. However, the job advertisement is explicitly aimed at all persons.\n\n\nDid we spark your interest?\n\nThen please click apply above to access our guided application process.\néˆ¥?more"
