g, and consistent project management standards. By closely collaborating with business, IT, and methodology stakeholders, the role drives tool adoption, usability, and continuous improvement across the global delivery landscape and impacts delivery efficiency and transparency.\n\nHow will you contribute to the success of DHL?\n\nTooling Design, Implementation \u0026 Optimization\n\n\n\nDefine, develop, and continuously improve the endéˆ¥و†ˆoéˆ¥و…¹nd tool stack that supports agile transformation delivery, and classic program and project reporting.\nDesign and configure intuitive, scalable tool-supported processes, turning complex requirements into clear workflows, templates, and guidance.\nImplement tools in collaboration with IT partners and related processes in alignment with business, functional, and IT stakeholders\nSupport technical integrations across tools (e.g., between BPM, Jira, workflow engines, automation platforms, process mining tools).\nEnsure system performance, stability, and smooth operation.\n\n\n\nAgile Coaching \u0026 Team Support\n\n\n\nCoach project teams on agile practices and help them effectively apply and ensure seamless usage across the organization.\nDrive harmonized tool adoption globally, ensuring consistency, usability, and continuous improvement across the project management ecosystem.\nEquip teams with the skills and guidance needed to leverage their expertise and deliver efficiently across regions and functions.\n\n\n\nProgram \u0026 Delivery Enablement\n\n\n\nSupport the Senior Director Methodology \u0026 Project Tools in driving successful program delivery and enhancing project management standards.\nCollaborate with the central PMO and the core functional and IT teams to align on program needs, ensure consistent methodology adoption, and coordinate training and onboarding activities.\n\n\n\nDo you have what it takes?\n\n\n\nRelevant university degree, Bachelor/ Master in Business Administration, Information Technology or similar.