        "jd":  "Req ID:517042\n\nAt Alstom, we understand transport networks and what moves people. From high-speed trains, metros, monorails, and trams, to turnkey systems, services, infrastructure, signalling and digital mobility, we offer our diverse customers the broadest portfolio in the industry. Every day, 80,000 colleagues lead the way to greener and smarter mobility worldwide, connecting cities as we reduce carbon and replace cars.\n\nCould you be the full-time Requirements Manager (f/m/d) in Hamburg or Berlin weéˆ¥وھ™e looking for?\n\nYour future role\n\nTake on a new challenge and apply your technical expertise in a cutting-edge field. Youéˆ¥وھ’l work alongside collaborative, innovative, and solution-oriented teammates.\n\nYouéˆ¥وھ’l play a key role in driving the consistency and quality of requirements across complex railway projects. You work closely with cross-functional teams across engineering, project management, and quality to ensure traceability, alignment, and successful delivery throughout the project lifecycle.\n\nWeéˆ¥وھ’l look for you to:\n\n\nDefine and drive the requirements management strategy across all project phases\nEnsure consistency, quality, and traceability of requirements from customer specifications to delivery\nCoordinate stakeholders in drafting, aligning, and validating requirements\nManage requirement changes and assess their impact on scope, timelines, and costs\nEnsure data quality and integrate external inputs across systems and teams\nMonitor progress, risks, and deviations, supporting informed project decision-making\nContribute to continuous improvement of requirements management tools, processes, and best practices\n\n\nAll About You\n\nWe value passion and attitude over experience. Thatéˆ¥وھڑ why we donéˆ¥وھ› expect you to have every single skill. Instead, weéˆ¥وھ‌e listed some that we think will help you succeed and grow in this role:\n\n\nHold a degree in a technical field or equivalent practical experience\nBring experience in engineering projects across different project phases\nDemonstrate knowledge of requirements management methodologies and tools\nCommunicate effectively and collaborate across multidisciplinary teams\nStructure priorities, manage complexity, and navigate competing objectives\nTake ownership, make decisions, and contribute to continuous improvement\nSpeak fluent German and English\n\n\nThings youéˆ¥وھ’l enjoy\n\nJoin us on a life-long transformative journey éˆ¥?the rail industry is here to stay, so you can grow and develop new skills and experiences throughout your career. Youéˆ¥وھ’l also:\n\n\nExperience a dynamic and meaningful work environment with a permanent role at a global leader in rail transportation\nContribute to innovative and impactful projects shaping the future of sustainable transport\nWork with international, cross-functional teams and supportive colleagues\nTake ownership of your career and explore development opportunities across functions, projects, and countries\nBenefit from our strong investment in your growth through award-winning learning at Alstom University\nWork in modern offices in Hamburg or Berlin with excellent public transport connections\nOptimise your work-life balance with flexible working hours and hybrid working models\nReceive a competitive remuneration package including 30 days of vacation, company pension, and subsidised éˆ¥و·’eutschlandticketéˆ¥و¼’nThrive in an inclusive workplace with mentoring programmes, diversity \u0026 inclusion initiatives, and engaging employee activities\n\n\nYou donéˆ¥وھ› need to be a train enthusiast to thrive with us. We guarantee that when you step onto one of our trains with your friends or family, youéˆ¥وھ’l be proud. If youéˆ¥وھ™e up for the challenge, weéˆ¥وھ‡ love to hear from you!\n\nImportant to note\n\nAs a global business, weéˆ¥وھ™e an equal-opportunity employer that celebrates diversity across the 63 countries we operate in. Weéˆ¥وھ™e committed to creating an inclusive workplace for everyone.\néˆ¥?more"
