        "jd":  "We help the world run better\n\nAt SAP, we keep it simple: you bring your best to us, and we\u0027ll bring out the best in you. We\u0027re builders touching over 20 industries and 80% of global commerce, and we need your unique talents to help shape what\u0027s next. The work is challenging éˆ¥?but it matters. You\u0027ll find a place where you can be yourself, prioritize your wellbeing, and truly belong. What\u0027s in it for you? Constant learning, skill growth, great benefits, and a team that wants you to grow and succeed.\n\nWhat You\u0027ll Build\n\nIn this role, you act as the senior delivery anchor for customer-facing, forward-deployed engagements. Embedded directly with SAPéˆ¥وھڑ most strategic customers, you lead the end-to-end delivery of complex, high-stakes AI initiatives, from early discovery and rapid prototyping through production deployment and scaling.\n\nYou are accountable for delivery outcomes, customer trust, and execution excellence. Operating at the intersection of business, engineering, and AI, you translate ambiguity into structured execution, ensuring that what is built works in the customeréˆ¥وھڑ real environmentéˆ¥و”پcross data, compliance, integration, and organizational constraints.\n\nIn This Role, You Will\n\n\nLead all phases of the customer engagement lifecycle, from discovery and scoping through delivery, client acceptance, and scale-out.\nOwn project scope, timelines, risks, and outcomes, ensuring delivery aligns with agreed success criteria and business objectives.\nDrive implementation excellence and customer adoption, ensuring delivered solutions meet technical, operational, and business expectations.\nUnderstand customerséˆ¥?businesses and industry-specific challenges and translate them into sustainable solutions.\nServe as the primary delivery interface for senior customer stakeholders, including executive leadership, building trust and managing expectations.\nEstablish tight, outcome-focused delivery rhythms, including frequent demos, transparent progress tracking, and proactive risk management.\nNavigate complex customer environments, balancing ambition with real-world constraints such as data readiness, compliance, and system integration.\nFeed field learnings back into SAP product and engineering teams, converting delivery insights into reusable playbooks and roadmap input.\n\n\nWhat You Bring\n\n\nYou demonstrate a proactive approach to leveraging AI in everyday workflows, ensuring highéˆ¥و†…uality outputs through thoughtful context design and system integration.\nDemonstrated ability to apply deep industry and/or E2E process knowledge to lead complex, customer-facing engagements. Acts as the senior delivery anchor, translating business objectives into executable delivery decisions and owning outcomes across forward-deployed implementations.\nProven ability to work in an Agentic AI context, shaping and applying AI agents that act autonomously within defined boundaries, collaborate with human stakeholders, and deliver measurable business outcomes in customer-centric environments.\nExtensive experience in project or program management within enterprise software, AI delivery, or customer-facing environments.\nProven ability to lead ambiguous, high-impact engagements from first customer interaction to production-ready solutions.\nStrong capability to operate in customer-embedded settings, navigating executive stakeholders, organizational complexity, and delivery pressure.\nDelivery mindset with high ownership, bias for action, and accountability for outcomes end-to-end.\nExcellent problem-solving and communication skills, with the ability to translate customer needs into actionable execution plans for technical teams.\nStrong understanding of agile delivery approaches and experience coordinating across engineering, AI/ML, product, and go-to-market teams.\nSolid awareness of enterprise AI deployment realities, including data readiness, model limitations, compliance, and integration considerations.\nYou demonstrate a proactive approach to leveraging AI in everyday workflows, ensuring high-quality outputs through thoughtful context design and system integration.\n\n\nWhere You Belong\n\nYou will be part of aéˆ¥ç—‌rowing AI and industry expert teaméˆ¥ç—™edicated to serving customers across the region (Americas, Europe, Asia). We are building a collaborative, high-impact environment that brings together deep AI expertise, strong industry knowledge, and regional understanding to help customers innovate, transform, and lead in their markets.\n\nThis team thrives on working together to turn complex business challenges into practical, scalable solutions. You will find an environment that valueséˆ¥ç——uriosity, ownership, and continuous learning, where new ideas are encouraged and real-world impact matters. This is a place for people who enjoy building something new. You will thrive here if you areéˆ¥ç——ustomer-centric, motivated by meaningful outcomes, and comfortable navigating ambiguityéˆ¥ç— n a fast-evolving AI landscape.\n\nWe work closely with decision-makers, challenge assumptions with data, and give data scientists room to influence strategyéˆ¥و”ڈot just produce analysis. We value sharp thinking, business curiosity, and clear communication.\n\nBring out your best\n\nSAP innovations help more than four hundred thousand customers worldwide work together more efficiently and use business insight more effectively. Originally known for leadership in enterprise resource planning (ERP) software, SAP has evolved to become a market leader in end-to-end business application software and related services for database, analytics, intelligent technologies, and experience management. As a cloud company with two hundred million users and more than one hundred thousand employees worldwide, we are purpose-driven and future-focused, with a highly collaborative team ethic and commitment to personal development. Whether connecting global industries, people, or platforms, we help ensure every challenge gets the solution it deserves. At SAP, you can bring out your best.\n\nWe win with inclusion\n\nSAPéˆ¥وھڑ culture of inclusion, focus on health and well-being, and flexible working models help ensure that everyone éˆ¥?regardless of background éˆ¥?feels included and can run at their best. At SAP, we believe we are made stronger by the unique capabilities and qualities that each person brings to our company, and we invest in our employees to inspire confidence and help everyone realize their full potential. We ultimately believe in unleashing all talent and creating a better world.\n\nSAP is committed to the values of Equal Employment Opportunity and provides accessibility accommodations to applicants with physical and/or mental disabilities. If you are interested in applying for employment with SAP and are in need of accommodation or special assistance to navigate our website or to complete your application, please send an e-mail with your request to Recruiting Operations Team: Careers@sap.com.\n\nFor SAP employees: Only permanent roles are eligible for the SAP Employee Referral Program, according to the eligibility rules set in the SAP Referral Policy. Specific conditions may apply for roles in Vocational Training.\n\nAI Usage in the Recruitment Process\n\nFor information on the responsible use of AI in our recruitment process, please refer to our Guidelines for Ethical Usage of AI in the Recruiting Process.\n\nPlease note that any violation of these guidelines may result in disqualification from the hiring process.\n\nRequisition ID: 453843 | Work Area: Consulting and Professional Services | Expected Travel: 0 - 10% | Career Status: Professional | Employment Type: Regular Full Time | Additional Locations:\n\n\néˆ¥?more"
